# React Composition and Performance Rules

- Minimize `useEffect`; prefer declarative data flow and derived values.
- Split large components into focused child components.
- Do not execute child-specific logic in parent components.
- Keep root/parent components orchestration-focused and render-light.
- Prevent unnecessary parent re-renders that cascade to unrelated children.

## Intent
Use composition to isolate logic and keep update scope local.
